$Fonseca clearly beat the throw from Cochrane but was called out by Ump Campbell for interfering with the play by running out of line.  The fans were incensed at Campbell not knowing about the interference ruling.  They were egged on by Mgr Peckinpaugh and Coach Shanks who ran in from the coaching lines.  Cleveland players surrounded Campbell and the park was in an uproar.  A hundred bottles were thrown from the RF stands; police were summoned to restore order.

umpchange,9,ump3b,(None) $Game was delayed when more pop bottles descended on Ump Campbell.  Ump Ormsby was knocked unconscious when a bottle struck him on the head. GM Billy Evans succeeded in quieting the crowd to some extent as Ormsby was helped from the field.  Players of both teams were helping the groundskeeper staff to clear the field of bottles.  A chorus of boos greeted Ump Campbell upon resumption of play. Joe Boley and Coach Bill Gleason were also injured by thrown bottles.

Hit 1st pitch high over RF wall;  Babe's 30th this season and 500th career HR.  The ball landed on Lexington Ave and was recovered by Mr. Jake Geiser. Later, the lucky Geiser met with Ruth who offered him $20 and two new autographed balls for it.  Geiser accepted.
